<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="1196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1196">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/158</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Edwards</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-10T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 10, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department suggests you confer with Immigration Inspector, as it is
                            understood he has standing instructions regarding refuge. Department has
                            no funds at its disposal that could be used to assist Chinese.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>